{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3aace0fe-93dc-4c63-be66-d003003ac187","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\nMTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`. Instead, the test executable itself accepts filters. With `dotnet test`, pass them via `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests\" --filter \"Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nEach `--filter` is ANDed together. The operators are the same (`~` for contains, `=` for exact match), but `&` compound expressions in a single string aren't supported — use multiple `--filter` flags instead.\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` → `[Category]` for category filtering\nxUnit v3 replaced `[Trait(\"Category\", \"...\")]` with a first-class `[Category]` attribute. The MTP filter `Category=Smoke` expects this. Update your test class:\n\n```diff\n-[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n+[Category(\"Smoke\")]\n```\n\n### Summary of CI change\n\n```diff\n-dotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n+dotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests\" --filter \"Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWant me to apply the `[Category]` change to your test file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1d2436e1-19ff-4c0b-9ef6-6ba918806e48","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"E843:13E67C:27815BC:29FA149:6A04942D"},"id":"d0937005-a0d0-4609-a7c4-edd58cbcd137","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:48.244Z","parentId":"4ad5ce19-f753-4899-b5c0-ad25506b49c2"}
